In the project at `/tmp/sv-138cb7fc27604ec8bedc08be4428e031/before/`, make the following targeted changes to fix AOT/trim warnings. Use the `edit` tool for each change. Read each file first to get the exact text.

### 1. ArmOperation.cs — Fix IL2090 and IL2087 on `IsResource<T>()`

The `IsResource<T>()` method uses reflection (`typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)`). These require `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` on the `T` generic parameter.

Add the annotation on `IsResource<T>()` and on all methods that call it (`Rehydrate<T>` and `RehydrateAsync<T>`).

Changes needed:
- Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` to the usings if not already present
- Change the signature of `IsResource<T>()` to:
  ```csharp
  private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
  ```
- Change the signature of `Rehydrate<T>` to:
  ```csharp
  public static ArmOperation<T> Rehydrate<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull
  ```
- Change the signature of `RehydrateAsync<T>` to:
  ```csharp
  public static async Task<ArmOperation<T>> RehydrateAsync<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull
  ```

### 2. GenericOperationSource.cs — Fix IL2087

The class `GenericOperationSource<T>` uses `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)`. Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` to the class's generic parameter.

Changes needed:
- The file already has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;`
- Change the class declaration to:
  ```csharp
  internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
  ```

### 3. ArmEnvironment.cs — Fix IL2026/IL3050 on `ToString()`

Line 80: `public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);`

Replace with manual JSON:
```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    return $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\"}}";
}
```

### 4. ArmClientOptions.cs — Fix IL2026/IL3050 on `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<...>>`

Line 52: `var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);`

Replace with `JsonDocument`-based parsing:
```csharp
using var profileDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
var allProfile = profileDoc.RootElement;
var armProfile = allProfile.GetProperty("resource-manager");
```

But then the code below uses `allProfile["resource-manager"]` and iterates as a dictionary. We need to adapt the iteration code too. Here's the full method body replacement. The current method body (inside the `using (Stream stream = ...)` block) is:
```csharp
var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span;
var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
var armProfile = allProfile["resource-manager"];
foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile)
{
    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Key;
    var element = keyValuePair.Value;

    foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
    {
        var apiVersion = apiVersionProperty.Name;
        foreach (var resourceTypeItem in apiVersionProperty.Value.EnumerateArray())
        {
            string resourceTypeName = default;
            foreach (var property in resourceTypeItem.EnumerateObject())
            {
                if (property.NameEquals("resourceType"))
                {
                    resourceTypeName = property.Value.GetString();
                    break;
                }
            }
            var resourceType = $"{namespaceName}/{resourceTypeName}";
            ResourceApiVersionOverrides[resourceType] = apiVersion;
        }
    }
}
```

Replace with:
```csharp
using var profileDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
var armProfile = profileDoc.RootElement.GetProperty("resource-manager");
foreach (var namespaceProperty in armProfile.EnumerateObject())
{
    var namespaceName = namespaceProperty.Name;
    var element = namespaceProperty.Value;

    foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
    {
        var apiVersion = apiVersionProperty.Name;
        foreach (var resourceTypeItem in apiVersionProperty.Value.EnumerateArray())
        {
            string resourceTypeName = default;
            foreach (var property in resourceTypeItem.EnumerateObject())
            {
                if (property.NameEquals("resourceType"))
                {
                    resourceTypeName = property.Value.GetString();
                    break;
                }
            }
            var resourceType = $"{namespaceName}/{resourceTypeName}";
            ResourceApiVersionOverrides[resourceType] = apiVersion;
        }
    }
}
```

Note: The `var span = ...` line and `var allProfile = ...` and `var armProfile = ...` lines change. The `foreach` body needs to change from iterating `Dictionary<string, JsonElement>` to iterating `JsonElement` using `EnumerateObject()`. But looking at the code more carefully, `element` was already a `JsonElement` (the `Dictionary<string, JsonElement>` value), so the inner loop (`element.EnumerateObject()`) already works. We just need to iterate the outer dict differently.

### 5. ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs — Fix IL2026/IL3050

Line 30 calls `builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration)` which is marked with `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`.

Add these attributes to the method:
```csharp
[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming.")]
[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime.")]
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
    where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
```

Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` to the usings if not already present.

### 6. LRO files — Fix IL2026/IL3050 on `ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>()`

Four files have `ModelReaderWriter.Write(...).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>()` which uses `JsonSerializer.Deserialize` internally.

Replace with `JsonDocument`-based parsing in these files:
- `ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperation.cs` line 61
- `ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperationOfT.cs` line 61
- `Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperation.cs` line 61
- `Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperationOfT.cs` line 61

In each file, replace:
```csharp
var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>();
return lroDetails["id"];
```
with:
```csharp
using var lroDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default));
return lroDoc.RootElement.GetProperty("id").GetString();
```

Also add `using System.Text.Json;` to the usings of each file if not already present.

### 7. ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization.cs — Fix JsonSerializer calls for ManagedServiceIdentityType and UserAssignedIdentity

File: `Common/Custom/Models/ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization.cs`

**Line 31**: `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType, jOptions);`

The custom converter (`ManagedServiceIdentityTypeConverter`) writes `"type"` property name and string value. We need to inline this logic but also handle the `jOptions` parameter which may carry a `ManagedServiceIdentityTypeV3Converter`.

Replace with direct converter invocation:
```csharp
if (jOptions != null)
{
    var converter = (JsonConverter<ManagedServiceIdentityType>)jOptions.GetConverter(typeof(ManagedServiceIdentityType));
    converter.Write(writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType, jOptions);
}
else
{
    writer.WritePropertyName("type"u8);
    writer.WriteStringValue(ManagedServiceIdentityType.ToString());
}
